{
  "texts": [
    "Our CRISPR screen reveals NHEJ as a major backup pathway for tolerance of TMZ-induced DNA damage in RAD18 -/-cells.",
    "Pharmacological inhibition of DNA-PK, or knockout of the PRKDC gene increases TMZ sensitivity of RAD18 -/-cells.",
    "Therefore, further work with orthotopic xenograft models is required to validate our in vitro finding that co-inhibition of TLS and NHEJ pathways might sensitize GBM cells to standard treatments in vivo.",
    "Our finding that RAD18 is important for tolerance of TMZinduced DNA damage yet has different mutagenic activities on the distinct TMZ-induced lesions (O 6 mG, N 7 mG and N 3 mA) is highly unexpected and unprecedented.",
    "O 6 mG is a highly mutagenic DNA lesion 62."
  ]
}